HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_SYMBOL: The selected symbol is the graphical representation of the entity type and appears alongside the entity name and on the maps.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_PIN: The selected pin is how the entity is identified on the map.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_PIN_TIP: When creating an asset, select one pin type for fieldwork assets and a different pin type for reference assets.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_GEOMETRY: Determines if the asset is a point or a line.

CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPING_WORKFLOW.MAIN_CONTENT: Determines when a user is directed to map an asset.
CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPING_WORKFLOW.IMMEDIATE_CONTENT: After creating an asset, the user is directed to the map. The user may map the asset at that moment or navigate back to the asset list and map the asset at a later moment.
CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPING_WORKFLOW.LATER_CONTENT: After creating an asset, the user remains within the asset list. The user may map the asset at a later moment.

CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.MAIN_CONTENT: The selected option determines if assets can be created when scanning a material traceability barcode and which type of barcode is supported.
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.NONE_CONTENT: Barcode scanning will not trigger the creation of the asset type.
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.SPECIFIC_CONTENT_PART_1: Barcode that contains a specific string triggers the creation of the asset type. The option requires a RegEx definition in the
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.SPECIFIC_CONTENT_PART_2: field to specify the particular string (exact or partial) used to parse the custom barcode.
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.CATALOG_INDEX_CONTENT_PART_1: Barcode that contains a catalog index triggers the creation of this asset type. The option requires a RegEx definition in the
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.CATALOG_INDEX_CONTENT_PART_2: field to specify the parsed catalog index location out of the scanned barcode.
CONFIG_EDITOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT.ASTM_CONTENT_PART_1: A standard ASTM F2897 barcode format trigger the creation of the asset type. The option requires matching to one or more ASTM categories selected in the

HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_REGEX_FOR_BARCODE_SUPPORT_: Enter a RegEx (regular expression) pattern to define a parsed sequence that extracts specific data from the barcode type format. The extracted data is used for identifying and creating the entity.
The RegEx pattern depends on the selected option in the Barcode Support field ( Specific String or Catalog Index).
The maximum length of the RegEx sequence is 512 bytes.
Provide a RegEx that supports Safari (IOS) and Chrome (Android) while verifying it on both browsers before applying it.
Enter a RegEx (regular expression) pattern to define a parsed sequence that extracts specific data from the barcode type format. The extracted data is used within the custom field.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_MATCH_TO_ASTM_CATEGORY_PAR: The optional ASTM categories mapped for the asset type are available for selection.
The selected ASTM category (or more) determine which categories to match when scanning standard ASTM barcode for asset creation.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_FORM_ATTAINABILITY: The selected option determines whether the form type can be attached to one or more assets.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_CAPTURE_BACKGROUND_INFO: When enabled, the location of the user is captured in the background while creating this form type. The location information is stored as metadata and is not visible within the Locusview platform.

CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPABILITY.MAIN_CONTENT: Determines whether a work unit can be mapped as a whole or if each asset within the work unit must be mapped individually.
CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPABILITY.MAPPABLE_CONTENT: Assets created within the work unit are mapped as part of the same network and not individually. The display order in which assets are listed reflects the order in which they are installed. When mapping the work unit, a user captures a pin at the beginning and the end of the network. Additional pins between the beginning and end may also be captured, but a pin is not required for each asset.
CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPABILITY.NOT_MAPPABLE_CONTENT: Assets created within the work unit are individually mapped as distinct entities.
CONFIG_EDITOR_MAPPABILITY.TIP: Mappable work units are often used for pipelines as the order of assets installation is critical, and only a few anchor points are required for assembly.

HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_LINE: Determines how lines appear when mapped.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_HELPER_TITLE_PART_1: The Helper buttons may be used to provide users with additional information helping them complete their work.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_HELPER_TITLE_PART_2: The helper title appears at the top of the screen when the user selects the helper button.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_HELPER_TEXT_PART_1: The Helper buttons may be used to provide users with additional information that will help them complete their work.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_HELPER_TEXT_PART_2:
The helper text appears below the helper title when the user selects the helper button. There is no limit to the number of characters the helper text may contain. 
Helper text can be provided in HTML for stylized content.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_SECTION_ALIAS: Defines a distinct header for the entity section.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_FIELD_ALIAS: Defines a distinct header for the entity field.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_UNIQUE_VALUE: When enabled, a user can save and sync the entity only when the value entered in this field is unique from all customized field instances within the specific entity type for the associated work order.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_PART_OF_CATALOG: When enabled, the field is a part of the Company Catalog associated with this asset type.  The Company Catalog data is managed in the Resources module.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_PART_OF_CU: When enabled, the field will be a part of the Compatible Units Library as an attribute of the Compatible Unit Records.  The Compatible Units Library is managed in the Resources module.
HELPER_TEXT.SUM_BY_TITLE: The Sum By field defines the calculation method of the compatible unit aggregation. The options are :
HELPER_TEXT.SUM_BY_QUANTITY: Quantity: the CU is aggregated from the number of derived assets set in the work order.
HELPER_TEXT.SUM_BY_FIELD: Specific Field: the CU is aggregated from the selected field's work order data. The optional fields are derived from the CU's Linked Entity.

CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.MAIN_CONTENT: Determines where the list type is required based on the location of its content source.
CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.LOCAL_LIST_CONTENT: The listing content variables are located in the particular field and defined locally.
CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.SHARED_LIST_CONTENT_PART_1: The list content and variables are located in a shared list defined in.
CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.SHARED_LIST_CONTENT_PART_2: and can be used many times for different entities. The selected list in the entity field references the actual source list values in the
CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.SHARED_LIVE_CONTENT_PART_1: The list content and variables are set by selecting the list name in the entity field. The list name refers to a shared live list managed in the
CONFIG_EDITOR_LIST_TYPE.SHARED_LIVE_CONTENT_PART_2: module where the content frequently changes.

HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_WHEN_FIELD: Defines the field that triggers the conditional parameter.
HELPER_TEXT.CONFIG_EDITOR_WAS_FIELD_OUT_WITH: Defines the condition that must be met within the triggering field ("When Field").
